<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="196" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[430,1829,423,1421]" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">
I take great pleasure in naming this species in honor of the collector, 0. H. Swezey. It is allied to 
<taxonomicName authority="(Alexander)" baseAuthorityName="Alexander" box="[917,1730,1223,1263]" class="Insecta" family="Tipulidae" genus="Linionia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albitarsis" subGenus="Liinonia">
<emphasis box="[917,1476,1223,1263]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Linionia (Liinonia) albitarsis</emphasis>
(Alexander)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[432,580,1273,1315]" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Limonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[432,580,1273,1315]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">Limonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(L.) 
<taxonomicName authority="Alexander" authorityName="Alexander" box="[710,1138,1273,1315]" class="Insecta" family="Limoniidae" genus="Dicranomyia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subalbitarsis">
<emphasis box="[710,928,1273,1315]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="196">subalbitarsis</emphasis>
Alexander
</taxonomicName>
, of the East Indies, differing in the small size and in the possession of two rostral spines on the ventral dististyle of the male hypopygium.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
